==Production==

===Pre-production===
In March 2011, [[Summit Entertainment]] picked up the rights for ''Divergent'' with [[Douglas Wick]] and Lucy Fisher's production company Red Wagon Entertainment.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://hollywoodcrush.mtv.com/2011/03/18/twilight-divergent/|title=Summit Entertainment's Post-'Twilight' Plans Are 'Divergent'|accessdate=June 6, 2013}}</ref>
[[Neil Burger]] was announced as the director on August 23, 2012.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.empireonline.com/News/story.asp?nid=34975 |title=Neil Burger Wants To Be Divergent |magazine=[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]] |date=August 23, 2012 |first=James |last=White |accessdate=May 24, 2013}}</ref> [[Evan Daugherty]], who co-wrote the screenplay with [[Vanessa Taylor]], said, "I get hung up on the toughness of the movie but of equal importance is the love story between Tris and Four. It's inherently and inextricably linked to Tris' character journey. There will be plenty of sexual tension and chemistry, but it's important that all of that stuff doesn't just feel like it's thrown in, but that it all helps Tris grow as a character."<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://blog.bookish.com/divergent-movie-scoop-screenwriter-evan-daugherty-spills-on-the-adaptation |title='Divergent' Movie Scoop: Screenwriter Evan Daugherty Spills on the Adaptation|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref> Daugherty further added, "It's tricky because the book is a very packed read with a lot of big ideas. So, distilling that into a cool, faithful two-hour movie is challenging. Not only do you have to establish five factions, but you have to acknowledge that there's a sixth entity, which is the divergent, and you also have the factionless. So there's a world that really has to be built out for the big screen<U+2026> the movie is going to do it a little more efficiently."<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.hypable.com/2013/03/14/divergent-screenwriter-vanessa-taylor-evan-daughtery/ |title='Game of Thrones' writer Vanessa Taylor joins 'Divergent' to co-write script|accessdate=July 20, 2013}}</ref> Author [[Veronica Roth]] said about the script of the film: "Reading a script is a really interesting experience. I'd never read a script before. I was really impressed by how closely it stuck to the general plot line of the book."<ref>{{cite web | date = May 2013 | author = Christina Radish |url= http://collider.com/veronica-roth-divergent-movie-interview/ |title= Author Veronica Roth Talks Divergent, the Film's Casting, How Neil Burger's Vision Compares to Her Own, the Final Book Allegiant, and More | archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20130619130256/http://collider.com/veronica-roth-divergent-movie-interview/ | archivedate = 2013-06-19 |accessdate=June 6, 2013}}</ref>

Initially, the budget of the film was $40 million but [[Lionsgate]] later increased it to $80 million (which finally changed to $85 million) due to the success of ''[[The Hunger Games (film series)|The Hunger Games]]''. Analyst Ben Mogil said, "Divergent is more similar to ''Hunger Games'' in that the company owns the underlying economics (i.e. production) and the budget (at $80[million]<!-- brackets to show edited from original pointlessly abbreviated to "mn" -->) is more manageable."<ref>{{cite news|title=Analysts Boost Lionsgate Price Target on 'Ender's Game', 'Divergent' Prospects|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/analysts-boost-lionsgate-price-target-428316|publisher=reelchicago.com|accessdate=June 8, 2013|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|date=March 13, 2013}}</ref>

===Casting===
[[File:Theo James Divergent premiere.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Theo James]] was cast as Tobias "Four" Eaton, winning the role over several other considered actors.]]
On October 22, 2012 it was announced that [[Shailene Woodley]] had landed the lead role of Beatrice "Tris" Prior.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.j-14.com/posts/shailene-woodley-talks-divergent-movie-casting-5968 |title=Shailene Woodley Talks 'Divergent' Movie Casting |accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref> [[Lucas Till]], [[Jack Reynor]], [[Jeremy Irvine]], [[Alex Pettyfer]], [[Brenton Thwaites]], [[Alexander Ludwig]] and [[Luke Bracey]] were all considered for the role of Tobias "Four" Eaton.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.deadline.com/2012/11/who-has-divergent-chemistry-with-shailene-woodley/ |title=Who Has 'Divergent' Chemistry With Shailene Woodley?|publisher=Deadline.com|date=November 14, 2012|author=Fleming Jr, Mike|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jack-reynor-lands-starring-role-409850 |title=Jack Reynor Lands Starring Role in 'Transformers 4'|accessdate=June 8, 2013 | work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Borys |last=Kit}}</ref> On March 15, 2013, it was announced that [[Theo James]] had been cast as Four.<ref name="ew-four">{{cite journal|last=Vilkomerson|first=Sara|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/03/15/divergent-four-theo-james/ |title='Divergent' has found its 'Four'! Theo James talks about starring in the next big YA franchise|journal=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref>

Though James was 10 years older than the character when cast, Roth praised his casting: "I was sure within seconds: this was 'Four', no question. Theo is able to capture 'Four's' authority and strength, as well as his depth and sensitivity." She also mentions the chemistry between him and Shailene: "He is a perfect match for Shailene's incredibly strong presence as Tris. I'm thrilled!"<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.divergentfans.com/profiles/blogs/veronica-roth-and-lionsgate-movie-studio-respond-to-theo-james-ca|title=Veronica Roth and Lionsgate Movie Studio Respond to Theo James Casting in The Divergent Movie|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref> The producers said about his casting: "We took our time to find the right actor to fill the role of Four, and Theo is definitely the perfect fit. Veronica has crafted a truly iconic character in Four and we cannot wait to begin production and bring him and this story to life for millions of fans around the world."<ref name="ew-four" />

On March 11, 2013, it was announced that the roles of Tori, Christina, and Caleb had gone to [[Maggie Q]], [[Zo<U+00EB> Kravitz]], and [[Ansel Elgort]] respectively.<ref>http://www.hypable.com/2013/03/11/divergent-movie-casting-tori-caleb-christina/</ref> [[Ray Stevenson (actor)|Ray Stevenson]], [[Jai Courtney]] and [[Aaron Eckhart]] were announced to be in talks to join the cast on March 15, 2013.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.empireonline.com/News/story.asp?nid=36822 |title=Aaron Eckhart May Be Divergent |magazine=Empire |date=March 15, 2013 |first=James |last=White |accessdate=May 24, 2013}}</ref> Stevenson and Courtney joined the cast as Marcus Eaton and Eric.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a465938/die-hard-5-star-jai-courtney-joins-shailene-woodley-in-divergent.html|title='Die Hard 5' star Jai Courtney joins Shailene Woodley in 'Divergent'|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref> That same day, [[Miles Teller]] was cast as Peter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hypable.com/2013/03/15/divergent-peter-casting-miles-teller/|title=Follow-up: Miles Teller will play Peter in <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> movie}}</ref> [[Kate Winslet]] was announced to be in talks on January 24, 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.empireonline.com/News/story.asp?nid=36296 |title=Kate Winslet May Be Divergent |date=January 24, 2013 |first=James |last=White |accessdate=May 24, 2013 |magazine=Empire}}</ref> Later, it was confirmed that she would portray Jeanine Matthews.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/kate-winslet-cast-young-adult-film-divergent-article-1.1295922 |title=Kate Winslet cast in young adult film 'Divergent|publisher=[[Daily News (New York)]]|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref> Talking about playing the negative character for the first time, Winslet said, "I'm no idiot. The idea went through my head that I have never played a baddie before, I was almost kind of surprised." Since Winslet joined filming late, she used that distance from her co-stars to appear aloof on the first day of her shoot. "I wanted to break it and say, 'It's OK, I'm really fun. I promise.' But I thought, just for today, I'd let them think that I am a complete bitch."<ref name="z">{{cite news |url= http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2013/07/16/divergent-kate-winslet-pregnant/2507183/|title=On set of 'Divergent,' Kate Winslet is pregnant and mean|accessdate=June 8, 2013 | work=USA Today|first1=Bryan|last1=Alexander}}</ref> Winslet was five months pregnant during the shooting of the film and her pregnancy was concealed using various props. According to Burger, "We had to be very strategic in the way that we shot her. She always had some sort of file or case in her hand that was sort of protecting, you know, her bump."<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.yahoo.com/movies/revealed-how-kate-winslet-concealed-her-pregnancy-92087306107.html |title= Revealed: How Kate Winslet Concealed Her Pregnancy While Filming 'Divergent' |accessdate= 30 August 2014}}</ref>  On March 25, 2013, [[Ben Lamb]] was cast as Edward, [[Ben Lloyd-Hughes]] as Will, and [[Christian Madsen]] as Al.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Divergent-Movie-Casts-Al-Edward-36586.html|title=Divergent Movie Casts Al, Edward And Will}}</ref> In April 2013, [[Ashley Judd]] and [[Tony Goldwyn]] joined the cast as Natalie and Andrew Prior, Beatrice's parents.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/04/13/divergent-ashley-judd-cast/|title='Divergent': Ashley Judd cast as Natalie Prior}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/04/15/tony-goldwyn-joins-divergent/|title=Tony Goldwyn joins 'Divergent'<U+2014>Exclusive}}</ref>

===Filming===
[[File:Giant Wheel Navy Pier Chicago.jpg|thumb|The Ferris wheel scene in ''Divergent'' was filmed at [[Navy Pier]].]]

Filming began in [[Chicago]] on April 16, 2013 and concluded on July 16, 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pagetopremiere.com/2013/04/images-video-from-divergent-movie-set-in-chicago-houses-in-abnegation-what-do-you-think-this-is/ |title=Picture and video from 'Divergent' movie set in Chicago: Houses in Abnegation? What do you think this is? |date=April 26, 2013 |work=Page to Premiere |first=Kimmy |last=West |accessdate=May 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url= http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/04/24/shailene-woodley-divergent-first-look/ |title=First Look: Shailene Woodley faces knives in 'Divergent' -- Exclusive Photo |date=April 24, 2013 |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |first=Sara |last=Vilkomerson |accessdate=May 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thewrap.com/movies/article/comic-con-2013-divergent-star-shailene-woodley-not-super-hero-movie-104396|title=Comic-Con 2013: Shailene Woodley Says 'Divergent' Is Not a Superhero Movie |accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> Virtually all production photography took place in Chicago; many of the interior locations were filmed at Cinespace Chicago Film Studios.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-06-23/entertainment/ct-ent-0624-luis-20130623_1_veronica-roth-transformers-divergent|title=Blockbuster summer awaits movie-set fans Divergent, Jupiter Ascending and Transformers bring Hollywood to Chicago|accessdate=20 July 2013 | work=Chicago Tribune|first=Luis|last=Gomez|date=June 23, 2013}}</ref> Scenes for the "choosing ceremony" were shot at [[Seventeenth Church of Christ, Scientist (Chicago, Illinois)|17th Church of Christ, Scientist, Chicago]] on East Wacker in downtown Chicago.,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thedivergent.net/index.php/87-divergent-film/402-new-filming-location|title=NEW Filming Location!|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> with outdoor shots taken at [[Pioneer Court]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2014-03-06/entertainment/chi-divergent-shailene-woodley-ferris-wheel-20140306_1_ansel-elgort-shailene-woodley-theo-james|title='Divergent' stars talk Rahm Emanuel, Blackhawks and riding the 'L'|work=Chicago Tribune|date=March 6, 2014|author=Gomez, Luis|accessdate=14 September 2014}}</ref>  Filming also took place at the [[Navy Pier]] Ferris Wheel; the entire area was treated with dirt and rust to appear more [[dystopian]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pagetopremiere.com/2013/04/divergent-set-photos-ferris-wheel-scene-being-filmed-on-navy-pier/|title='Divergent' movie set photos: Hugely anticipated ferris wheel scene being filmed on Navy Pier|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> Additional scenes were shot at 57th Street and Ellis Avenue near the [[University of Chicago]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2013/06/14/divergent-filming-around-the-university-of-chicago-this-weekend/|title='Divergent' filming around the University of Chicago & 600 S Wells St this weekend|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> at Federal Street where fake [[Chicago 'L'|L tracks]] were constructed<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2013/05/26/new-photos-and-videos-of-divergent-filming-in-chicago-this-weekend/|title=New photos and videos of 'Divergent' filming in Chicago this weekend!|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> and at [[Michigan Avenue (Chicago)|Michigan Avenue]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2013/05/23/new-divergent-filming-locations-spotted-in-chicago-for-may-24-2013/|title=Upadte New 'Divergent' filming locations spotted in Chicago for May 24, 2013|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref>

For the Abnegation sector, the production team constructed the set on [[Wells Street (Chicago)|Wells Street]] in downtown Chicago.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.divergentfans.com/profiles/blogs/divergent-movie-set-update-more-images-from-the-abnegation-set|title=Divergent Movie Set Update: More Images from The Abnegation Set|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> In late June, filming took place at 1500 S Western Avenue and 600 S. Wells Street, Chicago.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2013/06/21/video-of-divergent-filming-at-600-s-wells-st-in-chicago/|title=Video of 'Divergent' filming at 600 S. Wells St in Chicago|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> In the last schedule, filming moved to the [[Chicago River]] and continued at Lake Street Bridge, Wacker Drive and LaSalle Street Bridge.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2014/01/05/divergent-is-filming-additional-scenes-in-los-angeles-this-month/|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> is filming additional scenes in Los Angeles this month|accessdate=20 July 2013}}</ref> Filming wrapped on July 16, 2013.<ref name="'Divergent' hits Comic-Con!">{{cite news|url=http://www.usatoday.com/videos/life/movies/2013/07/31/2570235/|title='Divergent' hits Comic-Con!|accessdate=January 17, 2014 | work=USA Today}}</ref> On January 24, 2014, additional filming began in [[Los Angeles]], finishing on January 26, 2014, which officially became the last day of shooting.<ref name="'Divergent' hits Comic-Con!"/>

===Post-production===
[[Post-production]] work began after filming wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.yahoo.com/video/divergent-hits-comic-con-220606958.html|title='Divergent' Hits Comic-Con!| publisher = [[Yahoo! News]]|accessdate=July 20, 2013}}</ref> On July 18, Summit and Lionsgate issued a joint statement announcing the film would be released in [[IMAX]] format: "We're delighted to continue our successful collaboration with IMAX, with whom we have already partnered on the global blockbuster ''Hunger Games'' and ''Twilight Saga'' franchises, and we're especially pleased that we can introduce our newest young adult franchise, ''Divergent'', to the movie going public in the premium IMAX format that celebrates its status as a special and memorable event."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://collider.com/divergent-movie-imax-release/|title=Neil Burger's DIVERGENT Starring Shailene Woodley, Theo James, and Kate Winslet to Be Released in IMAX| publisher = Collider.com |accessdate=July 20, 2013}}</ref>

==Music==
{{Main|Divergent (soundtrack)}}
The score for ''Divergent'' was composed by [[Junkie XL]] and executive produced by his longtime mentor [[Hans Zimmer]]. Randall Poster served as the film's music supervisor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hypable.com/2013/11/13/divergent-score-hans-zimmer-producer/|title=Hans Zimmer to produce Junkie XL<U+2019>s <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> score|accessdate=March 3, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2013/11/11/junkie-xl-to-score-divergent/|title=Junkie XL to Score <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019>|accessdate=March 3, 2014}}</ref> The original soundtrack was released on March 11, 2014, while the Original Score of the film was released on March 18, 2014, by [[Interscope Records]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universalmusic.com/news/detail/2716|title=Interscope Records to Release Soundtrack and Score to Summit Entertainment<U+2019>s Highly Anticipated Feature Film Divergent|accessdate=March 3, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://online.wsj.com/article/PR-CO-20140225-908137.html|title=Interscope Records To Release Original Motion Picture Soundtrack And Score To Summit Entertainment's Highly Anticipated Feature Film Divergent On March 11|accessdate=March 3, 2014 | work=The Wall Street Journal|date=February 25, 2014}}</ref>

==Distribution==

===Marketing===
The first image of Shailene Woodley as Beatrice "Tris" Prior was revealed by ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' on April 24, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/04/24/shailene-woodley-divergent-first-look|title=First Look: Shailene Woodley Faces Knives in 'Divergent' Adaptation|last=Anderton|first=Ethan|date=April 24, 2013|publisher=''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''|accessdate=August 21, 2013}}</ref> A few seconds sneak preview footage of the film was shown at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.thefactionfour.net/2013/05/divergent-film-footage-was-shown-at.html|title=Divergent film footage was shown at Cannes Film Festival |accessdate= June 6, 2013}}</ref> On June 7, ''Entertainment Weekly'' released a still of Theo James (Four) showing the Dauntless initiates around their new headquarters.<ref>{{cite journal |url= http://insidemovies.ew.com/2013/06/07/divergent-first-picture-theo-james-four/|title=New 'Divergent' photo! Here is the first picture of (drumroll) Theo James as Four -- Exclusive|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref> The magazine released several more stills on July 19.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/gallery/0,,20647938_20710254,00.html#21347889|title='Divergent': Tris and Four Pics!|accessdate=July 20, 2013 | work=Entertainment Weekly|date=June 19, 2013}}</ref> On July 16, ''[[USA Today]]'' released the first image of Kate Winslet as Jeanine Matthews.<ref name="z" />

On July 18, 2013 Summit held a sold-out [[San Diego Comic-Con]] panel in Hall H. Shailene Woodley, Theo James, Maggie Q, Zoe Kravitz, Ansel Elgort, Ben Lloyd-Hughes, Amy Newbold, Miles Teller, Christian Madsen, director Neil Burger, and author Veronica Roth attended the panel and answered fan questions, along with the showing of exclusive film clips.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.yahoo.com/blogs/movie-talk/comic-con-2013-first-footage-young-adult-sensation-041859921.html|title=First Footage From YA Adaptation 'Divergent' Shown to Fans|accessdate= July 20, 2013}}</ref>

On August 22, 2013, a sneak peek of the first [[teaser trailer]] was released by [[MTV]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://screenrant.com/divergent-movie-teaser-trailer-image/|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Teaser Image and Trailer Preview Promise Something Big|accessdate=August 23, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hypable.com/2013/08/22/divergent-movie-trailer-mtv-vmas/|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> movie trailer to debut at this Sunday<U+2019>s MTV VMAs?|accessdate=August 23, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Divergent-Movie-Teaser-Image-Promises-Something-Big-Coming-MTV-VMAs-39118.html |title=Divergent Movie Teaser Image Promises Something Big Coming To The MTV VMAs|accessdate=August 23, 2013}}</ref> The full teaser was released on August 25, 2013 during the pre-show of the [[MTV Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S6HHCxLZftQ|title=Divergent official trailer|accessdate=August 26, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/divergent-first-trailer-debuts-mtv-614097|title='Divergent': First Trailer Debuts During MTV VMAs Pre-Show (Video)|accessdate=August 26, 2013 | work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Sophie|last=Schillaci|date=August 25, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.ropeofsilicon.com/divergent-trailer-mtv-video-music-awards-vma-watch/|title=Watch: First 'Divergent' Trailer and 9 New Pictures|accessdate=August 26, 2013}}</ref> Two official posters featuring Woodley and James as Tris and Four and highlighting their tattoos were released on September 23, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.latinospost.com/articles/28391/20130925/divergent-movie-news-update-summit-entertainment-unveils-first-two-posters.htm|title='Divergent' Movie News Update: Summit Entertainment Unveils First Two Posters|accessdate=September 25, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.hypable.com/2013/09/23/divergent-movie-posters-tris-four-tattoos/|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> releases two gorgeous posters highlighting Tris, Four, and their tattoos|accessdate=September 25, 2013}}</ref> Neil Burger released the full official [[Trailer (promotion)|trailer]] on November 13, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://geektyrant.com/news/divergent-action-packed-full-trailer|title=Divergent - Action packed full trailer|accessdate=November 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buzzsugar.com/Divergent-Full-Trailer-32429876|title=The Full Divergent Trailer Is Everything We Hoped For|accessdate=November 19, 2013}}</ref> On February 4, 2014 Shailene Woodley and Theo James released the final trailer for the film during their appearance on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/506985/shailene-woodley-and-theo-james-tease-final-divergent-trailer-on-jimmy-kimmel-live|title=Shailene Woodley and Theo James Premiere Final Divergent Trailer on Jimmy Kimmel Live|accessdate=February 5, 2014}}</ref>

The marketing campaign for the film cost at least $50 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/24/business/media/divergent-ticket-sales-justify-a-franchise.html?_r=1|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Ticket Sales Justify a Franchise|accessdate=March 24, 2014 | work=The New York Times|first=Brooks|last=Barnes|date=March 23, 2014}}</ref>

===Release===
On its first day of advance ticket sales, the film sold half of its tickets.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/03/divergent-tracking-to-huge-50m-to-60m-weekend-three-weeks-out-pre-sales-outstanding-300-and-mr-peabody-also-strong-for-weekend-bows/ |title={{-'}}Divergent' Tracking To Huge $50M<U+2013>$60M Weekend Three Weeks Out; Pre-Sales Outstanding; '300' And 'Mr. Peabody' Also Strong For Weekend Bows | date=March 5, 2014|author=Busch, Anita |publisher=[[Deadline.com]]  |accessdate=March 17, 2014}}</ref>

===Home media===
''Divergent'' was released on DVD and Blu-ray on August 5, 2014.<ref name="youtube.com"/> Prior to its DVD release, a deleted scene from the film featuring [[Miles Teller]] as [[List of The Divergent trilogy characters#Peter Hayes|Peter Hayes]] and Ben Lamb as [[List of The Divergent trilogy characters#Edward|Edward]] was released on July 30, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/07/30/divergent-deleted-scene/|title=Movies Here's a deleted scene that was too gross for 'Divergent'|accessdate=September 17, 2014}}</ref>

==Reception==

===Box office===
''Divergent'' earned $150,947,895 in North America, and $137,228,004 in other countries, for a worldwide total of <!-- Update this to match Infobox -->$288,175,899.<ref name="mojo" />

On its opening weekend, the film attained the No. 1 spot in domestic and worldwide box office rankings by [[Rentrak]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=293311959|title=Teen Sci-Fi Franchise 'Divergent' Debuts With $56M|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/ae/movies/2014/03/24/Divergent-based-on-young-adult-book-series-is-No-1/stories/201403240028|title='Divergent,' based on young adult book series, is No. 1|accessdate=March 24, 2014 | work=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|date=March 23, 2014}}</ref> The film grossed $4.9 million in late night screenings, on Thursday March 20, 2014.<ref name="debut">{{cite web|url=http://www.thewrap.com/divergent-box-office/|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Debuts to $4.9 Million, Lionsgate Greenlights <U+2018>Insurgent<U+2019>|accessdate=March 22, 2014}}</ref> On its opening day, the film grossed $22.8 million in the United States (including the Thursday night gross).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://variety.com/2014/film/news/box-office-divergent-dominates-with-22-8-million-friday-gods-not-dead-surprises-at-no-3-1201142827/|title=Box Office: <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Dominates With $22.8 Million Friday, <U+2018>God<U+2019>s Not Dead<U+2019> Surprises at No. 3|accessdate=March 22, 2014 | work=Variety}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/03/22/box-office-update-divergent-earns-22-8-million-friday/|title=Box office update: 'Divergent' earns $22.8 million on Friday|accessdate=March 22, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3803|title=Friday Report: 'Divergent' Scores $22.8 Million, 'God's Not Dead' Surprises|accessdate=March 22, 2014}}</ref> ''Divergent'' accumulated $54,607,747 from 3,936 theaters at an average of $13,873 per theater, on its opening weekend in the United States and Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=weekend&id=divergent.htm|title=Divergent (2014) Box Office Results|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/03/23/box-office-report-divergent/|title=Box office report: 'Divergent' heads straight for $56 million win; 'God's Not Dead' inspires $8.6 million|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2014/03/divergent-the-topped-weekend-box-office.html |title=Divergent Topped the Weekend Box Office|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref> and grossed $1.7 million internationally from four territories, with a worldwide total of <!-- opening weekend total DO NOT UPDATE -->$56,307,747.<!-- DO NOT UPDATE see below --><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.marketwatch.com/story/rentrak-announces-worldwide-box-office-results-for-weekend-of-march-23-2014-2014-03-23 |title=Rentrak Announces Worldwide Box Office Results for Weekend of March 23, 2014|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref><ref name="rentrak">{{cite web|url=http://www.rentrak.com/section/movies_and_tv_everywhere/top_entertainment_rankings.html#1|title=Worldwide Box Office|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.redorbit.com/news/entertainment/1113101776/rentrak-announces-worldwide-box-office-results-for-weekend-of-march-8/ |title=Rentrak Announces Worldwide Box Office Results for Weekend of March 23, 2014|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref>

===Critical response===
{{Anchor|Critics|Critical reception}} 
''Divergent'' received mixed reviews from critics. Review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]] gives the film a 41% rating based on reviews from 196 critics, with an average score of 5.4/10. The site's consensus states: "With an adherence to YA formula that undercuts its individualistic message, ''Divergent'' opens its planned trilogy in disappointingly predictable fashion."<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/divergent/|title=Divergent (2014) |publisher = [[Flixster]]|work= [[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate = 2014-05-02 }}</ref> [[Metacritic]] gives the film a score of 48 based on reviews from 38 critics, indicating "mixed or average reviews".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.metacritic.com/movie/divergent| title=Divergent: Reviews (2014) | publisher = [[CBS Interactive]] | work = [[Metacritic]] | accessdate = 2014-03-17
}}</ref> Audiences surveyed by CinemaScore were more receptive to the film, giving it a CinemaScore grade of "A". The survey group was 69% female and half of the audience was over 25.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-divergent-breaks-ya-690460 | work=The Hollywood Reporter | first=Pamela | last=McClintock | title=Box Office: 'Divergent' Breaks YA Curse With $56 Million Debut; 'Muppets 2' Bombs | date=March 23, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.thewrap.com/divergent-box-office-shailene-woodley-theo-james-franchise-born | title= <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Scores $56 Million Box-Office Opening, <U+2018>A<U+2019> CinemaScore <U+2013> And a Franchise Is Born (Video)|accessdate=March 24, 2014}}</ref>

The main criticisms of the film was its generic execution and predictable plot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tdn.com/lifestyles/film-review-divergent-off-to-slow-predictable-start/article_ea337b02-b303-11e3-8f49-001a4bcf887a.html|title=Film Review: 'Divergent' off to slow, predictable start|accessdate=September 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.providencejournal.com/features/entertainment/movies-tv/20140321-movie-review-divergent-doesnt-veer-from-predictable-path.ece|title=Movie Review: <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> doesn<U+2019>t veer from predictable path|accessdate=September 11, 2014}}</ref> Bruce Diones of ''[[The New Yorker]]'' called it, "barely diverting",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorker.com/arts/reviews/film/divergent_burger|title=Divergent (2014): Review|accessdate=September 11, 2014}}</ref> and Jordan Adler of ''We Got This Covered'' said it was a, "plodding and generic dystopian drama".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wegotthiscovered.com/movies/divergent-review/|title=Divergent Review|accessdate=September 11, 2014}}</ref>

Though the film overall received a mixed reception, many critics praised Shailene Woodley and Theo James for their portrayals as Beatrice Prior and Tobias Eaton. According to Todd Gilchrist of [[Indiewire|The Playlist]], "Woodley makes for more than uncertain enough of a hero to add detail and meaning to the implosion of this world", adding that "there's little artifice to her performance, and the mundane honesty of her reactions create a believability that the world would otherwise lack." Speaking of James's performance, Gilchrist adds that he "manages the considerable accomplishment of seeming like a real grown-up man" and that he "makes the character's transformation from hardass to collaborator seem natural, if inevitable".<ref name="blogs.indiewire.com">{{cite web |url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/review-divergent-starring-shailene-woodley-kate-winslet-miles-teller-more-20140316 | title= Review: 'Divergent' Starring Shailene Woodley, Kate Winslet, Miles Teller & More |accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> Drew McWeeny at [[HitFix]] said, "it helps that [they] got Woodley and James in the leads. [Woodley's] like a walking empathy battery, wide-open emotionally, easy to read and enormously appealing", also adding that James is "incredibly natural onscreen".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitfix.com/motion-captured/review-divergent-succeeds-largely-due-to-shailene-woodley-and-theo-james|title=Review: 'Divergent' succeeds largely due to Shailene Woodley and Theo James|accessdate=August 8, 2014}}</ref>

Andrew Osmond of ''[[SFX (magazine)|SFX]]'' magazine was more receptive to the film, calling it "an often entertaining, and sometimes very interesting, piece of teen SF".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.sfx.co.uk/2014/04/04/divergent-review/ | title= <U+2018>Divergent REVIEW|accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> Andy Lea of ''Daily Star'' wrote that "the satire is not as sharp as that of ''[[The Hunger Games (film)|The Hunger Games]]'' and the training scenes borrow heavily from the much smarter ''[[Ender's Game (film)|Ender's Game]]''. But it's also stylish, tense and surprisingly pacy."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/movies/372047/Review-and-trailer-Divergent-12A-delivers-teenage-kicks | title= Review and trailer: Divergent (12A) delivers teenage kicks|accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> ''[[Orlando Weekly]]''{{'}}s Sam Allard gave the film a 3/5 rating, praising Shailene Woodley's performance by saying she "rescues and then raises up a film that could have been an utter disaster".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://m.orlandoweekly.com/film/film-version-of-divergent-is-a-worthy-effort-1.1656806 | title= Divergent |accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> Christy Lemire of RogerEbert.com agreed with this sentiment, writing, "the performances<U+2014>namely from stars Shailene Woodley and Theo James and Kate Winslet in a juicy supporting role<U+2014>always make the movie watchable and often quite engaging".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/divergent-2014 | title= Review - Divergent |accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> Michael O'Sullivan of ''[[The Washington Post]]'' felt that the film surpassed its source material, feeling that "it's rare that a movie is as good as the book on which it's based. It's even more unusual when it's better."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/divergent-movie-review-better-than-the-book-believe-it/2014/03/19/03b9bfe2-af75-11e3-96dc-d6ea14c099f9_story.html | title= 'Divergent' movie review: Better than the book? Believe it. |accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> Leigh Paatsch of the ''[[Herald Sun]]'' dubbed the film a "solid first-up effort for the ''Divergent'' franchise",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/movies/divergent-which-is-similar-to-the-hunger-games-is-the-movie-everyones-talking-about/story-fni0bv7o-1226878875910|title=Divergent, which is similar to The Hunger Games, is the movie everyone's talking about|accessdate=August 3, 2014}}</ref> and Margaret Pomeranz of ''[[At the Movies (Australian TV series)|At the Movies]]'' gave praise to director Neil Burger, stating that he "handles the action with aplomb".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/atthemovies/txt/s3970024.htm|title=Divergent: Review by Margaret Pomeranz|accessdate=August 3, 2014}}</ref>

The Playlist's Todd Gilchrist gave it a mixed review saying that it has "great ideas ... and some terrific character work, but it's given such uneven attention, alternately languished upon and glossed over".<ref name="blogs.indiewire.com"/> [[IGN]]'s Matt Patches gave it 5.8 out of 10, citing its similarities to other young adult films and contrived Dauntless plot line. He praised lead actors Theo James and Shailene Woodley's performances, judging that they "add personality and physicality to the limp script they're acting out".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/03/17/divergent-review | title= All Too Familiar | work = [[IGN Entertainment]] | publisher = [[News Corp.]] |accessdate = 2014-03-18}}</ref> Scott Mendelson of ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine echoed these sentiments, arguing that despite Woodley's excellent performance, "the generic story reduced a large portion of the mythology to irrelevancy". Mendelson believed that the film would please the novel's fanbase.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2014/03/16/review-divergent-will-please-its-fans/ |title=Review: 'Divergent' Isn't Different Enough|publisher = [[Forbes]] |accessdate = 2014-03-18 |first=Scott |last=Mendelson |date=March 16, 2014}}</ref>

