==Sequels==
{{Main|The Divergent Series: Insurgent}}
On May 7, 2013, Summit Entertainment revealed that a sequel based on ''[[Insurgent (novel)|Insurgent]]'' was in the works. Brian Duffield, writer of ''[[Jane Got a Gun]]'', was hired to write the script.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://collider.com/divergent-sequel-insurgent-brian-duffield/ |last=Trumbore|first=Dave|title=Summit Sets Brian Duffield to Pen DIVERGENT Sequel, INSURGENT|publisher=Collider.com|date=May 7, 2013|accessdate=May 8, 2013}}</ref> The sequel is scheduled to be released on March 20, 2015. The third film, based on ''[[Allegiant (novel)|Allegiant]]'', was initially announced as a single film scheduled for release on March 18, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://collider.com/gods-of-egypt-release-date/ |last=Trumbore|first=Dave|title=Summit Sets Release Dates for Divergent Threequel Allegiant, Plus Gods of Egypt and Step Up All In|publisher=Collider.com|date=December 16, 2013|accessdate=December 17, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.hypable.com/2013/12/16/allegiant-movie-release-date/ |last=Sims|first=Andrew|title=Summit sets March 2016 date for <U+2018>Allegiant,<U+2019> avoids a split (for now)|publisher=hypable.com|date=December 16, 2013|accessdate=January 5, 2014}}</ref> In December 2013, it was announced that Neil Burger will not return to direct the sequel, due to him still working on the first film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://variety.com/2013/film/news/divergent-director-neil-burger-wont-do-sequel-exclusive-1200966623/|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Director Neil Burger Won<U+2019>t Do Sequel but he will be co producer of insurgent and helping out (Exclusive)|accessdate=December 17, 2013 | work=Variety}}</ref> On February 11, 2014, it was announced that [[Robert Schwentke]] would take Burger's place for the next installment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://herocomplex.latimes.com/movies/divergent-sequel-insurgent-finds-director-in-robert-schwentke/#/0|title=Divergent<U+2019> sequel <U+2018>Insurgent<U+2019> finds director in Robert Schwentke |publisher=herocomplex.latimes.com |date=2014-02-23|accessdate=2014-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/02/robert-schwentke-insurgent-director-divergent-sequel/|title=Robert Schwentke To Direct <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Sequel <U+2018>Insurgent<U+2019>|publisher=Deadline.com |date=February 11, 2014|author=Fleming Jr, Mike}}</ref> <ref name="debut" /> <ref>{{cite web|title=<U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Sequel <U+2018>Insurgent<U+2019> Starts Filming in Atlanta May 27th!|url=http://www.fanbolt.com/divergent-sequel-insurgent-starts-filming-atlanta-may-27th/|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

On April 11, 2014, Summit Entertainment announced that the third film would split into two films titled ''The Divergent Series: Allegiant <U+2013> Part 1'' and ''The Divergent Series: Allegiant <U+2013> Part 2'', with ''Part 1'' scheduled to be released on March 18, 2016 and ''Part 2'' scheduled to be released on March 24, 2017.<ref>{{cite news| title=Lionsgate Splitting Third <U+2018>Divergent<U+2019> Book <U+2018>Allegiant<U+2019> into Two Films |url=http://variety.com/2014/film/news/lionsgate-splitting-third-divergent-book-allegiant-into-two-films-1201155988/ | work=Variety}}</ref> On December 5, 2014, it was announced that Robert Schwentke, will return to direct the ''Part 1''.<ref>{{cite news| title=<U+2018>Insurgent<U+2019> Director Robert Schwentke Returning for <U+2018>Allegiant Part 1<U+2032> (EXCLUSIVE) |url=http://variety.com/2014/film/news/insurgent-director-robert-schwentke-returning-for-allegiant-part-1-exclusive-1201372155/ | work=Variety}}</ref>

